  <refnamediv>
    <refname>linear</refname>
    <refpurpose>Linear output for Takagi-Sugeno fuzzy logic systems.</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>


<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Calling Sequence</title>
   <synopsis>
   y=linear(x,par)
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
   <varlistentry><term>x:</term>
      <listitem><para>matrix of real with size [m,n].</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>par:</term>
      <listitem><para>row vector with n+1 elements .</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
<literal>constant </literal> compute the linear output of a Takagi-Sugeno fls
due the evaluations of rules stored in <literal>x</literal>. This is a util
function.
   </para>
   <para>
The number of parameters are equal to the number of inputs plus 1.
   </para>
   <para>
The output have the form:
<literal>y=x*par(1:n)+ones(m,1)*par(n+1)</literal>
</para>
</refsection>

